ategory:Urdu theologians]]\n[[Category:Urdu writers from India]]\n[[Category:Indian male poets]]\n[[Category:Poets from Bihar]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "name_user": "Quebec99", "label": "safe", "comment": "fixed reference", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shamim_Hashimi"}
{"title_page": "The Gores Group", "text_new": "{{multiple issues|\n {{advert|date=September 2018}}\n {{prose|date=August 2019}}\n {{lead extra info|date=August 2019}}\n}}\n\n{{Infobox company\n| company_name        = The Gores Group, LLC\n| logo                = [[File:The Gores Group logo.png|200px|The Gores Group logo]]\n| type                = [[Limited liability company]]\n| foundation          = {{start date and age|1987}}\n| founder             = [[Alec Gores]], chairman & CEO\n| location            = [[Los Angeles, California]], [[United States]]\n| industry            = [[Financial services]]<br>[[Asset management]]\n| products            = [[Private equity]]\n| assets              = $3.7 billion\n| homepage            = [http://www.gores.com/ www.gores.com]|\n}}\n'''The Gores Group''' is a global [[private equity]] firm specializing in acquiring and partnering with mature and growing businesses. The company was founded in 1987 by its CEO and chairman, [[Alec Gores|Alec E. Gores]].\n\nHeadquartered in [[Los Angeles]], California, with offices in [[London]] and [[Boulder, Colorado]], the firm claimed to have approximately $2.0 billion in [[assets under management]] on September 30, 2016,<ref name=overview>{{cite web|url=http://www.gores.com/company/overview/|title=Overview|publisher=The Gores Group|accessdate=April 9, 2013}}</ref> and is investing from Gores Capital Partners III, L.P. and Gores Small Capitalization Partners, L.P., which have approximately $1.5 billion and $300 million in capital commitments, respectively. Since 1987, Gores has successfully acquired and operated more than 80 companies worldwide.<ref name=overview/>\n\nThe company's current portfolio as of 2015, includes technology, telecommunications, business services, industrial, healthcare, media & entertainment and consumer products companies.<ref name=overview/>\n\n{{toc limit}}\n\n== History ==\nIn 1978, Alec Gores founded Executive Business Systems, a hardware and software distributor, which he sold eight years later to establish what has become the Gores Group today.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.docstoc.com/docs/29742074/Fixer-upper-pro-loves-a-challenge/=3|title=Fixer-upper pro loves a challenge|work=Docstoc.com}}</ref>\n\nGores closed its first [[Institutional investor|institutional]] [[private equity fund]], Gores Capital Partners, L.P., in November 2003 with $400 million of committed capital.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://goliath.ecnext.com/coms2/gi_0199-3319570/Gores-Technology-Group-LLC-Closes.html=4|title=Manta - Rediscover America's Small Business|work=Manta}}</ref> The firm's second fund, Gores Capital Partners II, L.P. held a final closing in June 2007 with $1.3 billion of committed capital.<ref>[http://www.gores.com/news/current/news_fo_20110216.pdf \"Alec Gores: '100% devoted' to private equity\"], ''Fortune'', February 16, 2011</ref>\n\n===Timeline===\n====1978====\n* Alec Gores launches his own computer company, Executive Business System (EBS), with $10,000; eight years later, he sells EBS for approximately $2 million current.<ref name=\"www.gores.com\"/>\n\n====1987====\n* The Gores Group is founded by Alec Gores with the single vision to buy, fix and sell businesses.<ref>[http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapId=107629n \"Company Overview of the Gores Group LLC\"], ''Bloomberg Business Week''</ref>\n\n====1997====\n* Gores acquires Artemis, a subsidiary of [[Computer Sciences Corporation]] (NYSE: CSC).<ref>[http://aecnews.blogspot.com/2007/07/gores-technology-group-acquires-csc.html \"Gores Technology Group Acquires CSC Artemis\"], ''AECNews'' (archived), March 1, 1997</ref>\n* Gores completes its purchase of the Connection Machines business unit from [[Thinking Machines Corporation]].<ref>[http://www.gores.com/pressreleases/gores-technology-group-acquires-connection-machines-services-business-unit/ \"Gores Technology Group Acquires Connection Machines Services Business Unit\"], The Gores Group, April 16, 1997</ref>\n\n====1998====\n* Gores carves out certain assets of the [[Computer-integrated manufacturing|Computer Integrated Manufacturing]] (CIM) organization of [[Texas Instruments]] (NYSE:TXN); the portfolio company is later named Adventa Control Technologies.<ref>[https://sw.thecsiac.com/techs/abstract/159333 \"Gores Acquires TI CIM Unit\"], ''Software Intensive Systems Engineering'', June 15, 1998</ref>\n\n====2000====\n* Gores carves out [[The Learning Company]] and [[Mattel Interactive]] from [[Mattel]] and achieves an operating profit in the first 75 days of ownership.<ref>[http://www.sfgate.com/business/article/Learning-Co-Profits-From-Expense-Cuts-Novato-2945040.php \"Learning Co. Profits From Expense Cuts\"], ''SF Gate'', March 6, 2001</ref>\n\n==== 2001 ====\n* Gores acquires [[Verifone|VeriFone]] from Hewlett Packard Company.<ref>{{cite web|author=The Associated Press |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2001/05/11/business/gores-technology-to-acquire-verifone.html |title=Gores Technology to Acquire VeriFone - The New York Times |publisher=Nytimes.com |date=2001-05-11 |accessdate=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n\n====2003====\n* Netherlands-based Anker BV, an independent European supplier of point of sale solutions, is acquired, positioning Gores as an investor in European assets.<ref>[http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/gores-technology-group-announces-the-acquisition-of-anker-bv-74500207.html \"Gores Technology Group Announces the Acquisition of Anker B.V.\"], ''PR Newswire'', February 27, 2003</ref>\n* The firm launches Gores Capital Partners, its first private equity fund; to date,{{when|date=June 2014}} the combined Gores private equity funds have raised over $4 billion in committed capital.<ref name=\"www.gores.com\"/>\n\n====2004====\n* Gores opens its London office, after several years of investment activity in the U.K. and Europe.<ref name=\"www.gores.com\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.gores.com/|title=The Gores Group \u2013 The Gores Group}}</ref>\n\n====2007====\n* Gores closes on $1.3 billion in capital for its second institutional fund, Gores Capital Partners II, L.P.<ref>[http://articles.latimes.com/2007/jun/28/business/fi-gores28 \"Gores Fund is looking to close Smaller Deals\"], ''Los Angeles Times'', June 28, 2007</ref>\n\n====2008====\n* Gores announces joint venture partnership with [[Siemens AG]] for enterprise communication business.<ref>[https://www.bloomberg.com/apps/news?pid=newsarchive&sid=apt8SdmoOQyw \"The Gores Group and Siemens AG Complete Transaction\"], ''Bloomberg'', October 1, 2008</ref>\n\n====2010====\n* Sale of GCP II-owned [[Vincotech]]<ref>Wikipedia Vincotech Article (In German)</ref>  to [[Mitsubishi Electric]] demonstrates Gores\u2019 global reach.<ref>[http://www.pehub.com/92223/gores-group-completes-sale-of-vincotech-to-mitsubishi-electric/ \"Gores Group Completes Sale of Vinotech\"], ''PE Hub'', January 5, 2011</ref>\n\n====2011====\n* Gores sells Lineage Power to [[General Electric]] in what is the largest sale transaction in Gores\u2019 history.<ref>[https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-01-13/ge-energy-to-buy-gores-group-s-lineage-power-efficiency-for-520-million.html \"GE Energy to Acquire Gores Group's Lineage Power Holdings\"], ''Bloomberg'', January 13, 2011</ref>\n* Gores closes on $2.1 billion in capital commitments for its third institutional fund, Gores Capital Partners III, L.P.<ref>[http://www.cpifinancial.net/news/post/7544/the-gores-group-closes-2-billion-private-equity-fund- \"The Gores Group closes $2 billion private equity fund\"], ''CPI Financial''</ref>\n* Gores acquires an 81.25% majority interest in fashion company [[Mexx]] for $85 Million\n\n====2012====\n* Gores Small Capitalization Partners, L.P. sells $300 million in commitments, expanding Gores\u2019 resources for small and lower middle market investments.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20120307006224/en/Gores-Group-Debuts-Fund|title=The Gores Group Debuts New Fund|publisher=}}</ref>\n* Acquires [[Harris Broadcast]] from [[Harris Corporation]] in December.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://harris.com/press/article.asp?id=3558|title=Harris Corporation to Sell Broadcast Communications to The Gores Group for $225 Million|author=Harris Corporation|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n====2013====\n* Stock Building Supply goes public, marking Gores' first U.S. [[Initial public offering|IPO]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bizjournals.com/triangle/news/2013/06/18/stock-building-supply-to-go-public.html|title=Stock Building Supply files to go public|date=18 June 2013|work=Triangle Business Journal}}</ref>\n\n====2014====\n* Gores announces plans to close 34 subsidiaries of 45 in total located in Germany and being part of [[Unify (company)|Unify]]. Close downs are expected to be completed by Q2/2015.\n* On December 4, 2014, three holding companies of Mexx were declared bankrupt by the district court of Amsterdam. On December 5, 2014, a judge in the Netherlands declared 315 Mexx stores, which serves worldwide including 95 Locations in Canada, bankrupt. The stores are expected to remain open while the chain sells off merchandise.\n* In April, Gores acquires a 51% stake in [[Hovis]] Bread\n\n== Recognition ==\n* On December 17, 2013, at the 12th Annual M&A Advisor Awards Gala, The Gores Group was named winner of the \u201cM&A Deal of the Year\u201d (for transactions $500 million to $1 billion in size) for the acquisition of Stock Building Supply. Gores acquired the Company from Wolseley plc in May 2009 and priced a successful IPO in August 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://maadvisor.net/MANY/MANY-2013/12th-Annual%20MA-Advisor-Awards-Winners-Press-Release.pdf|title=M&A Advisor press release|website=maadvisor.net}}</ref>\n* On September 26, 2013, Cosmo Specialty Fibers was awarded the Chain-of-custody certification by the [[Programme for the Endorsement of Forest Certification]]. This certification recognizes Cosmo Specialty Fibers for using wood fiber sourced through sustainable forestry practices.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kbkw.com/modules/news/article.php?storyid=6038|title=Cosmo Specialty Fibers Awarded PEFC Chain-of-Custody Certification - Newstalk KBKW|publisher=}}</ref>\n* On August 29, 2013, in celebration of the recent [[initial public offering]] of its stock, Stock Building Supply\u2019s CEO, Jeff Rea, rang the opening bell of the [[New York Stock Exchange]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nasdaq.com/marketsite/marketsite-events-detail.aspx?fn=201308-open08292013.txt|title=NASDAQ MarketSite Event|publisher=}}</ref>\n* On August 20, 2013, [[Siemens Enterprise Communications]] announced that it has been named as a Leader in the 2013 Magic Quadrant for Unified Communications (UC) by [[Gartner]], Inc. Gartner evaluates a company based on its completeness of vision based on current and future market direction, innovation, customer needs, and competitive forces, and how well these map to Gartner\u2019s overall evaluation of the market.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marketwatch.com/story/siemens-enterprise-communications-positioned-as-a-leader-in-2013-magic-quadrant-for-unified-communications-2013-08-20|title=Siemens Enterprise Communications Positioned as a Leader in 2013 Magic Quadrant for Unified Communications|work=MarketWatch}}</ref>\n* On July 17, 2013, [[Enterasys Networks]], a Siemens Enterprise Communications Company, was ranked fourth in overall market share among leading Ethernet Edge Switch vendors by the Dell\u2019Oro Group\u2019s 1Q13 Enterprise Edge Report. Dell\u2019Oro group surveyed 30 Wireless LAN and 30 Ethernet Switch equipment vendors for this report.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nasdaq.com/press-release/enterasys-recognized-as-top-industry-leader-in-delloro-group-2013-enterprise-edge-report-20130717-00266|title=Latest News Headlines - NASDAQ.com|work=NASDAQ.com}}</ref>\n* On May 27, 2013, [[Ford Motor Company]] announced that it is working with Gores\u2019 Portfolio Company, Sage Automotive Interiors, to accelerate the development of recycled fabrics. Sage is Ford\u2019s largest fabric supplier in North America, and provides Ford with fabric made from industrial waste and clear plastic water bottles. The 2013 [[Ford Fusion (Americas)|Ford Fusion]] is the first vehicle sold around the world to use recycled fabrics.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/joannmuller/2013/05/27/fords-global-ambitions-include-turning-the-worlds-plastic-bottles-into-car-parts/|title=Ford's Global Ambitions Include Turning The World's Plastic Bottles Into Car Parts|author=Joann Muller|date=27 May 2013|work=Forbes}}</ref>\n* On October 1, 2012, The Gores Group received ''[[Private Equity International]]'''s Award for Operational Excellence in the TMT sector for Lineage Power. PEI\u2019s Operational Excellence Awards recognize and highlight the achievements in the industry.<ref>[http://www.peimedia.com/resources/PEI/Supplements%202012/PEI_OpExAwards2SEC.pdf \"PEI Operational Excellence Awards 2012\"], ''Private Equity International'', October 8, 2012</ref>\n* On June 19, 2011, The Gores Group won the Global M&A Network's Atlas Award for \"turnaround deal of the year\", for their acquisition of [[National Envelope Corporation]].<ref>[https://globalmanetwork.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/june19_2011.pdf \"National Envelope wins Private Equity Turnaround Deal of the Year Award\"], Turnaround Atlas Awards, June 19, 2011</ref>\n* On December 13, 2011, The Gores Group was named the winner of the Middle-Market Deal of the Year award ($50\u2013100 million) for their acquisition of Cosmo Specialty Fibers at the 10th Annual M&A Advisor Awards. The Gores Group was selected from 389 nominations and over 500 participating companies to receive this award.<ref>[http://www.maadvisor.net/conferences/2011-many/10th_annual_MA_Advisor_Awards-press-release.pd \"Winners Announced for the 10th Annual M&A Awards\"], ''The M&A Advisor', December 16, 2011</ref>\n\n== Representative transactions ==\n* January 27, 2014: The Gores Group announced that it has reached a conditional agreement with [[Premier Foods]] to operate its bread business as a stand-alone venture under the name of [[Hovis]] Limited in order to increase operational efficiencies and grow the Hovis brand.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foodmanufacture.co.uk/Business-News/Premier-Foods-launches-Hovis-partnership-with-Gores-Group|title=Premier Foods in Hovis partnership with US Gores Group|work=FoodManufacture.co.uk}}</ref>\n* August 14, 2013: Stock Building Supply Holdings, Inc. (Nasdaq:STCK) announced that it has closed its previously announced underwritten initial public offering of 7,000,000 shares of common stock at the price to the public of $14.00 per share. The underwriters exercised in their full option to purchase an additional 1,050,000 shares of common stock from certain selling stockholders, resulting in a total initial public offering size of 8,050,000 shares.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dwmmag.com/index.php/stock-building-supply-announces-closing-of-ipo/|title=Stock Building Supply Announces Closing of IPO - DWM/Shelter Magazine|publisher=}}</ref>\n* July 30, 2013: Gores\u2019 portfolio company, The Hay Group, announced that it had entered into an agreement to acquire Metallumform, an integrated manufacturer of forged machined automotive components with two plants in [[Germany]]. Terms of the transaction were not disclosed.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://eon.businesswire.com/news/eon/20130730006365/en/The-Gores-Group/The-Hay-Group/Metallumform|title=The Hay Group Announces the Acquisition of Metallumform|publisher=}}</ref>\n* January 2, 2013: The Gores Group announced that it had completed the acquisition of Therakos, Inc. from Ortho-Clinical Diagnostics, Inc.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20130102005173/en/Gores-Group-Completes-Acquisition-Therakos-Ortho-Clinical-Diagnostics|title=The Gores Group Completes the Acquisition of Therakos, Inc. from Ortho-Clinical Diagnostics, Inc. - Business Wire|publisher=}}</ref>\n* December 14, 2012: Charles Bank Capital Partners announced that it acquired United Road Services from The Gores Group for an undisclosed amount. Kathleen McCann, president and CEO, will continue to lead the company.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.charlesbank.com/news/2012/12_14_12.xml|title=News - Charlesbank|website=charlesbank.com}}</ref>\n* October 15, 2012: The Gores Group announced that it extended a binding offer to acquire Therakos, Inc. from [[Ortho-Clinical Diagnostics|Ortho-Clinical Diagnostics, Inc.]] Therakos is company developing products for [[extracorporeal photopheresis]] (ECP) [[immune modulation]] therapy. The terms of the transaction were not disclosed.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20121015005164/en/Gores-Group-Extends-Binding-Offer-Acquire-Therakos|title=The Gores Group Extends Binding Offer to Acquire Therakos, Inc. from Ortho-Clinical Diagnostics, Inc. - Business Wire|publisher=}}</ref>\n* August 17, 2011: [[The Carlyle Group]] announced that it had completed the acquisition of French-based [[Sagem]]com, a global high-technology group specializing in  broadband communications and  energy  activities, from The Gores Group. Carlyle said in a statement it now owned 70 percent of Sagemcom, while the company's management and employees had the remaining 30 percent. Sagemcom has more than 6,000 employees globally and posted sales of 1.4 billion euros in 2010.<ref>[https://www.reuters.com/article/2011/08/20/france-carlyle-sagecom-idUSLDE77J04820110820 \"Carlyle says finalises buy of France's Sagemcom from The Gores Group\"], ''Reuters'', August 20, 2011</ref>\n* May 9, 2011: The Gores Group announced that it partnered with management to acquire Sage Automotive Interiors, Inc., a supplier of specialty fabric materials for the automotive industry, a portfolio company of Azalea Capital, LLC.<ref>[https://finance.yahoo.com/news/The-Gores-Group-Acquires-Sage-bw-2397005636.html?x \"The Gores Group Acquires Sage Automotive Interiors\"], ''Yahoo Finance'', May 9, 2011</ref>\n* January 13, 2011: [[General Electric|General Electric Co.]] agreed to buy Lineage Power Holdings Inc. for $520 million from The Gores Group. Lineage supplies equipment that converts power to direct current from alternating current as well as power-module and data-center systems in the $20 billion [[micro power source]] industry.<ref>[https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-01-13/ge-energy-to-buy-gores-group-s-lineage-power-efficiency-for-520-million.html \"GE Energy to Acquire Gores Group's Lineage Power Holdings for $520 Million\"], ''Bloomberg'', January 13, 2011</ref>\n\n== Portfolio<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gores.com/portfolio/|title=Portfolio \u2013 The Gores Group|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref>==\n{{refimprove section|date=October 2018}}\n\n=== Active ===\n{{div col|colwidth=20em}}\n* [[AMI Entertainment Network]]<ref name=\"AMI\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.grbj.com/articles/88537-investment-firm-buys-jukebox-maker|title=Investment firm buys jukebox maker|access-date=2018-10-18}}</ref>\n* Cosmo Specialty Fibers, Inc\n* [[GatesAir]]\n* Hostess\n* Hovis Bakery\n* Imagine Communications\n* Melle Dachbaustoffe GmbH\n* Meridian\n* PAE\n* Turbineaero\n* US Farathane\n* Verra Mobility\n* Vitac{{Div col end}}\n\n=== Exited ===\n{{div col|colwidth=20em}}\n* Alliance Entertainment\n* Alpheus\n* Astadia\n* Avure Technologies\n* Big Strike\n* BMC\n* Brand-Rex\n* Cobridge Communications\n* Compudyne\n* Datablue\n* Diagnostic Health\n* DialGlobal\n* Elo Touch Solutions\n* equinox payments\n* etrali Trading Solutions\n* First Communications\n* Fotona\n* GTL\n* Glotel\n* Hay\n* inmac\n* J. Mendel\n* Lineage Power\n* [[Mexx]]\n* Millennium1 Solutions\n* National Envelope\n* Peoplenet\n* Powerwave Technologies\n* Proxicom\n* [[:nl:Real Software|Real Software]] ([[Belgium]])\n* Sage Automotive Interiors\n* Sagemcom\n* Scovill\n* Somero Enterprises, Inc.\n* The Clark Group, Inc.\n* Therakos, Inc.\n* Tweddle Group\n* Unify (formerly Siemens Enterprise Communication)\n* Unitedroad\n* Vincotech\n* Wire One Communications\n* Zmags\n{{Div col end}}\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official website|http://www.gores.com}}\n\n{{Private equity firms}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Gores Group}}\n[[Category:Private equity firms of the United States]]\n[[Category:Financial services companies established in 1987]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Los Angeles]]\n", "text_old": "{{multiple issues|\n {{advert|date=September 2018}}\n {{prose|date=August 2019}}\n {{lead extra info|date=August 2019}}\n}}\n\n{{Infobox company\n| company_name        = The Gores Group, LLC\n| logo                = [[File:The Gores Group logo.png|200px|The Gores Group logo]]\n| type                = [[Limited liability company]]\n| foundation          = {{start date and age|1987}}\n| founder             = [[Alec Gores]], chairman & CEO\n| location            = [[Los Angeles, California]], [[United States]]\n| industry            = [[Financial services]]<br>[[Asset management]]\n| products            = [[Private equity]]\n| assets              = $3.7 billion\n| homepage            = [http://www.gores.com/ www.gores.com]|\n}}\n'''The Gores Group''' is a global [[private equity]] firm specializing in acquiring and partnering with mature and growing businesses. The company was founded in 1987 by its CEO and chairman, [[Alec Gores|Alec E. Gores]].\n\nHeadquartered in [[Los Angeles]], California, with offices in [[London]] and [[Boulder, Colorado]], the firm claimed to have approximately $2.0 billion in [[assets under management]] on September 30, 2016,<ref name=overview>{{cite web|url=http://www.gores.com/company/overview/|title=Overview|publisher=The Gores Group|accessdate=April 9, 2013}}</ref> and is investing from Gores Capital Partners III, L.P. and Gores Small Capitalization Partners, L.P., which have approximately $1.5 billion and $300 million in capital commitments, respectively. Since 1987, Gores has successfully acquired and operated more than 80 companies worldwide.<ref name=overview/>\n\nThe company's current portfolio as of 2015, includes technology, telecommunications, business services, industrial, healthcare, media & entertainment and consumer products companies.<ref name=overview/>\n\n{{toc limit}}\n\n== History ==\nIn 1978, Alec Gores founded Executive Business Systems, a hardware and software distributor, which he sold eight years later to establish what has become the Gores Group today.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.docstoc.com/docs/29742074/Fixer-upper-pro-loves-a-challenge/=3|title=Fixer-upper pro loves a challenge|work=Docstoc.com}}</ref>\n\nGores closed its first [[Institutional investor|institutional]] [[private equity fund]], Gores Capital Partners, L.P., in November 2003 with $400 million of committed capital.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://goliath.ecnext.com/coms2/gi_0199-3319570/Gores-Technology-Group-LLC-Closes.html=4|title=Manta - Rediscover America's Small Business|work=Manta}}</ref> The firm's second fund, Gores Capital Partners II, L.P. held a final closing in June 2007 with $1.3 billion of committed capital.<ref>[http://www.gores.com/news/current/news_fo_20110216.pdf \"Alec Gores: '100% devoted' to private equity\"], ''Fortune'', February 16, 2011</ref>\n\n===Timeline===\n====1978====\n* Alec Gores launches his own computer company, Executive Business System (EBS), with $10,000; eight years later, he sells EBS for approximately $2 million current.<ref name=\"www.gores.com\"/>\n\n====1987====\n* The Gores Group is founded by Alec Gores with the single vision to buy, fix and sell businesses.<ref>[http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapId=107629n \"Company Overview of the Gores Group LLC\"], ''Bloomberg Business Week''</ref>\n\n====1997====\n* Gores acquires Artemis, a subsidiary of [[Computer Sciences Corporation]] (NYSE: CSC).<ref>[http://aecnews.blogspot.com/2007/07/gores-technology-group-acquires-csc.html \"Gores Technology Group Acquires CSC Artemis\"], ''AECNews'' (archived), March 1, 1997</ref>\n* Gores completes its purchase of the Connection Machines business unit from [[Thinking Machines Corporation]].<ref>[http://www.gores.com/pressreleases/gores-technology-group-acquires-connection-machines-services-business-unit/ \"Gores Technology Group Acquires Connection Machines Services Business Unit\"], The Gores Group, April 16, 1997</ref>\n\n====1998====\n* Gores carves out certain assets of the [[Computer-integrated manufacturing|Computer Integrated Manufacturing]] (CIM) organization of [[Texas Instruments]] (NYSE:TXN); the portfolio company is later named Adventa Control Technologies.<ref>[https://sw.thecsiac.com/techs/abstract/159333 \"Gores Acquires TI CIM Unit\"], ''Software Intensive Systems Engineering'', June 15, 1998</ref>\n\n====2000====\n* Gores carves out [[The Learning Company]] and [[Mattel Interactive]] from [[Mattel]] and achieves an operating profit in the first 75 days of ownership.<ref>[http://www.sfgate.com/business/article/Learning-Co-Profits-From-Expense-Cuts-Novato-2945040.php \"Learning Co. Profits From Expense Cuts\"], ''SF Gate'', March 6, 2001</ref>\n\n==== 2001 ====\n* Gores acquires [[Verifone|VeriFone]] from Hewlett Packard Company.<ref>{{cite web|author=The Associated Press |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2001/05/11/business/gores-technology-to-acquire-verifone.html |title=Gores Technology to Acquire VeriFone - The New York Times |publisher=Nytimes.com |date=2001-05-11 |accessdate=2019-08-21}}</ref>\n\n====2003====\n* Netherlands-based Anker BV, an independent European supplier of point of sale solutions, is acquired, positioning Gores as an investor in European assets.<ref>[http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/gores-technology-group-announces-the-acquisition-of-anker-bv-74500207.html \"Gores Technology Group Announces the Acquisition of Anker B.V.\"], ''PR Newswire'', February 27, 2003</ref>\n* The firm launches Gores Capital Partners, its first private equity fund; to date,{{when|date=June 2014}} the combined Gores private equity funds have raised over $4 billion in committed capital.<ref name=\"www.gores.com\"/>\n\n====2004====\n* Gores opens its London office, after several years of investment activity in the U.K. and Europe.<ref name=\"www.gores.com\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.gores.com/|title=The Gores Group \u2013 The Gores Group}}</ref>\n\n====2007====\n* Gores closes on $1.3 billion in capital for its second institutional fund, Gores Capital Partners II, L.P.<ref>[http://articles.latimes.com/2007/jun/28/business/fi-gores28 \"Gores Fund is looking to close Smaller Deals\"], ''Los Angeles Times'', June 28, 2007</ref>\n\n====2008====\n* Gores announces joint venture partnership with [[Siemens AG]] for enterprise communication business.<ref>[https://www.bloomberg.com/apps/news?pid=newsarchive&sid=apt8SdmoOQyw \"The Gores Group and Siemens AG Complete Transaction\"], ''Bloomberg'', October 1, 2008</ref>\n\n====2010====\n* Sale of GCP II-owned [[Vincotech]]<ref>Wikipedia Vincotech Article (In German)</ref>  to [[Mitsubishi Electric]] demonstrates Gores\u2019 global reach.<ref>[http://www.pehub.com/92223/gores-group-completes-sale-of-vincotech-to-mitsubishi-electric/ \"Gores Group Completes Sale of Vinotech\"], ''PE Hub'', January 5, 2011</ref>\n\n====2011====\n* Gores sells Lineage Power to [[General Electric]] in what is the largest sale transaction in Gores\u2019 history.<ref>[https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-01-13/ge-energy-to-buy-gores-group-s-lineage-power-efficiency-for-520-million.html \"GE Energy to Acquire Gores Group's Lineage Power Holdings\"], ''Bloomberg'', January 13, 2011</ref>\n* Gores closes on $2.1 billion in capital commitments for its third institutional fund, Gores Capital Partners III, L.P.<ref>[http://www.cpifinancial.net/news/post/7544/the-gores-group-closes-2-billion-private-equity-fund- \"The Gores Group closes $2 billion private equity fund\"], ''CPI Financial''</ref>\n* Gores acquires an 81.25% majority interest in fashion company [[Mexx]] for $85 Million\n\n====2012====\n* Gores Small Capitalization Partners, L.P. sells $300 million in commitments, expanding Gores\u2019 resources for small and lower middle market investments.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20120307006224/en/Gores-Group-Debuts-Fund|title=The Gores Group Debuts New Fund|publisher=}}</ref>\n* Acquires [[Harris Broadcast]] from [[Harris Corporation]] in December.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://harris.com/press/article.asp?id=3558|title=Harris Corporation to Sell Broadcast Communications to The Gores Group for $225 Million|author=Harris Corporation|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n====2013====\n* Stock Building Supply goes public, marking Gores' first U.S. [[Initial public offering|IPO]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bizjournals.com/triangle/news/2013/06/18/stock-building-supply-to-go-public.html|title=Stock Building Supply files to go public|date=18 June 2013|work=Triangle Business Journal}}</ref>\n\n====2014====\n* Gores announces plans to close 34 subsidiaries of 45 in total located in Germany and being part of [[Unify (company)|Unify]]. Close downs are expected to be completed by Q2/2015.\n* On December 4, 2014, three holding companies of Mexx were declared bankrupt by the district court of Amsterdam. On December 5, 2014, a judge in the Netherlands declared 315 Mexx stores, which serves worldwide including 95 Locations in Canada, bankrupt. The stores are expected to remain open while the chain sells off merchandise.\n* In April, Gores acquires a 51% stake in [[Hovis]] Bread\n\n== Recognition ==\n* On December 17, 2013, at the 12th Annual M&A Advisor Awards Gala, The Gores Group was named winner of the \u201cM&A Deal of the Year\u201d (for transactions $500 million to $1 billion in size) for the acquisition of Stock Building Supply. Gores acquired the Company from Wolseley plc in May 2009 and priced a successful IPO in August 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://maadvisor.net/MANY/MANY-2013/12th-Annual%20MA-Advisor-Awards-Winners-Press-Release.pdf|title=M&A Advisor press release|website=maadvisor.net}}</ref>\n* On September 26, 2013, Cosmo Specialty Fibers was awarded the Chain-of-custody certification by the [[Programme for the Endorsement of Forest Certification]]. This certification recognizes Cosmo Specialty Fibers for using wood fiber sourced through sustainable forestry practices.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kbkw.com/modules/news/article.php?storyid=6038|title=Cosmo Specialty Fibers Awarded PEFC Chain-of-Custody Certification - Newstalk KBKW|publisher=}}</ref>\n* On August 29, 2013, in celebration of the recent [[initial public offering]] of its stock, Stock Building Supply\u2019s CEO, Jeff Rea, rang the opening bell of the [[New York Stock Exchange]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nasdaq.com/marketsite/marketsite-events-detail.aspx?fn=201308-open08292013.txt|title=NASDAQ MarketSite Event|publisher=}}</ref>\n* On August 20, 2013, [[Siemens Enterprise Communications]] announced that it has been named as a Leader in the 2013 Magic Quadrant for Unified Communications (UC) by [[Gartner]], Inc. Gartner evaluates a company based on its completeness of vision based on current and future market direction, innovation, customer needs, and competitive forces, and how well these map to Gartner\u2019s overall evaluation of the market.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marketwatch.com/story/siemens-enterprise-communications-positioned-as-a-leader-in-2013-magic-quadrant-for-unified-communications-2013-08-20|title=Siemens Enterprise Communications Positioned as a Leader in 2013 Magic Quadrant for Unified Communications|work=MarketWatch}}</ref>\n* On July 17, 2013, [[Enterasys Networks|Entarasys Networks]], a Siemens Enterprise Communications Company, was ranked fourth in overall market share among leading Ethernet Edge Switch vendors by the Dell\u2019Oro Group\u2019s 1Q13 Enterprise Edge Report. Dell\u2019Oro group surveyed 30 Wireless LAN and 30 Ethernet Switch equipment vendors for this report.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nasdaq.com/press-release/enterasys-recognized-as-top-industry-leader-in-delloro-group-2013-enterprise-edge-report-20130717-00266|title=Latest News Headlines - NASDAQ.com|work=NASDAQ.com}}</ref>\n* On May 27, 2013, [[Ford Motor Company]] announced that it is working with Gores\u2019 Portfolio Company, Sage Automotive Interiors, to accelerate the development of recycled fabrics. Sage is Ford\u2019s largest fabric supplier in North America, and provides Ford with fabric made from industrial waste and clear plastic water bottles. The 2013 [[Ford Fusion (Americas)|Ford Fusion]] is the first vehicle sold around the world to use recycled fabrics.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/joannmuller/2013/05/27/fords-global-ambitions-include-turning-the-worlds-plastic-bottles-into-car-parts/|title=Ford's Global Ambitions Include Turning The World's Plastic Bottles Into Car Parts|author=Joann Muller|date=27 May 2013|work=Forbes}}</ref>\n* On October 1, 2012, The Gores Group received ''[[Private Equity International]]'''s Award for Operational Excellence in the TMT sector for Lineage Power. PEI\u2019s Operational Excellence Awards recognize and highlight the achievements in the industry.<ref>[http://www.peimedia.com/resources/PEI/Supplements%202012/PEI_OpExAwards2SEC.pdf \"PEI Operational Excellence Awards 2012\"], ''Private Equity International'', October 8, 2012</ref>\n* On June 19, 2011, The Gores Group won the Global M&A Network's Atlas Award for \"turnaround deal of the year\", for their acquisition of [[National Envelope Corporation]].<ref>[https://globalmanetwork.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/june19_2011.pdf \"National Envelope wins Private Equity Turnaround Deal of the Year Award\"], Turnaround Atlas Awards, June 19, 2011</ref>\n* On December 13, 2011, The Gores Group was named the winner of the Middle-Market Deal of the Year award ($50\u2013100 million) for their acquisition of Cosmo Specialty Fibers at the 10th Annual M&A Advisor Awards. The Gores Group was selected from 389 nominations and over 500 participating companies to receive this award.<ref>[http://www.maadvisor.net/conferences/2011-many/10th_annual_MA_Advisor_Awards-press-release.pd \"Winners Announced for the 10th Annual M&A Awards\"], ''The M&A Advisor', December 16, 2011</ref>\n\n== Representative transactions ==\n* January 27, 2014: The Gores Group announced that it has reached a conditional agreement with [[Premier Foods]] to operate its bread business as a stand-alone venture under the name of [[Hovis]] Limited in order to increase operational efficiencies and grow the Hovis brand.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foodmanufacture.co.uk/Business-News/Premier-Foods-launches-Hovis-partnership-with-Gores-Group|title=Premier Foods in Hovis partnership with US Gores Group|work=FoodManufacture.co.uk}}</ref>\n* August 14, 2013: Stock Building Supply Holdings, Inc. (Nasdaq:STCK) announced that it has closed its previously announced underwritten initial public offering of 7,000,000 shares of common stock at the price to the public of $14.00 per share. The underwriters exercised in their full option to purchase an additional 1,050,000 shares of common stock from certain selling stockholders, resulting in a total initial public offering size of 8,050,000 shares.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dwmmag.com/index.php/stock-building-supply-announces-closing-of-ipo/|title=Stock Building Supply Announces Closing of IPO - DWM/Shelter Magazine|publisher=}}</ref>\n* July 30, 2013: Gores\u2019 portfolio company, The Hay Group, announced that it had entered into an agreement to acquire Metallumform, an integrated manufacturer of forged machined automotive components with two plants in [[Germany]]. Terms of the transaction were not disclosed.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://eon.businesswire.com/news/eon/20130730006365/en/The-Gores-Group/The-Hay-Group/Metallumform|title=The Hay Group Announces the Acquisition of Metallumform|publisher=}}</ref>\n* January 2, 2013: The Gores Group announced that it had completed the acquisition of Therakos, Inc. from Ortho-Clinical Diagnostics, Inc.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20130102005173/en/Gores-Group-Completes-Acquisition-Therakos-Ortho-Clinical-Diagnostics|title=The Gores Group Completes the Acquisition of Therakos, Inc. from Ortho-Clinical Diagnostics, Inc. - Business Wire|publisher=}}</ref>\n* December 14, 2012: Charles Bank Capital Partners announced that it acquired United Road Services from The Gores Group for an undisclosed amount. Kathleen McCann, president and CEO, will continue to lead the company.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.charlesbank.com/news/2012/12_14_12.xml|title=News - Charlesbank|website=charlesbank.com}}</ref>\n* October 15, 2012: The Gores Group announced that it extended a binding offer to acquire Therakos, Inc. from [[Ortho-Clinical Diagnostics|Ortho-Clinical Diagnostics, Inc.]] Therakos is company developing products for [[extracorporeal photopheresis]] (ECP) [[immune modulation]] therapy. The terms of the transaction were not disclosed.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20121015005164/en/Gores-Group-Extends-Binding-Offer-Acquire-Therakos|title=The Gores Group Extends Binding Offer to Acquire Therakos, Inc. from Ortho-Clinical Diagnostics, Inc. - Business Wire|publisher=}}</ref>\n* August 17, 2011: [[The Carlyle Group]] announced that it had completed the acquisition of French-based [[Sagem]]com, a global high-technology group specializing in  broadband communications and  energy  activities, from The Gores Group. Carlyle said in a statement it now owned 70 percent of Sagemcom, while the company's management and employees had the remaining 30 percent. Sagemcom has more than 6,000 employees globally and posted sales of 1.4 billion euros in 2010.<ref>[https://www.reuters.com/article/2011/08/20/france-carlyle-sagecom-idUSLDE77J04820110820 \"Carlyle says finalises buy of France's Sagemcom from The Gores Group\"], ''Reuters'', August 20, 2011</ref>\n* May 9, 2011: The Gores Group announced that it partnered with management to acquire Sage Automotive Interiors, Inc., a supplier of specialty fabric materials for the automotive industry, a portfolio company of Azalea Capital, LLC.<ref>[https://finance.yahoo.com/news/The-Gores-Group-Acquires-Sage-bw-2397005636.html?x \"The Gores Group Acquires Sage Automotive Interiors\"], ''Yahoo Finance'', May 9, 2011</ref>\n* January 13, 2011: [[General Electric|General Electric Co.]] agreed to buy Lineage Power Holdings Inc. for $520 million from The Gores Group. Lineage supplies equipment that converts power to direct current from alternating current as well as power-module and data-center systems in the $20 billion [[micro power source]] industry.<ref>[https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-01-13/ge-energy-to-buy-gores-group-s-lineage-power-efficiency-for-520-million.html \"GE Energy to Acquire Gores Group's Lineage Power Holdings for $520 Million\"], ''Bloomberg'', January 13, 2011</ref>\n\n== Portfolio<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gores.com/portfolio/|title=Portfolio \u2013 The Gores Group|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref>==\n{{refimprove section|date=October 2018}}\n\n=== Active ===\n{{div col|colwidth=20em}}\n* [[AMI Entertainment Network]]<ref name=\"AMI\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.grbj.com/articles/88537-investment-firm-buys-jukebox-maker|title=Investment firm buys jukebox maker|access-date=2018-10-18}}</ref>\n* Cosmo Specialty Fibers, Inc\n* [[GatesAir]]\n* Hostess\n* Hovis Bakery\n* Imagine Communications\n* Melle Dachbaustoffe GmbH\n* Meridian\n* PAE\n* Turbineaero\n* US Farathane\n* Verra Mobility\n* Vitac{{Div col end}}\n\n=== Exited ===\n{{div col|colwidth=20em}}\n* Alliance Entertainment\n* Alpheus\n* Astadia\n* Avure Technologies\n* Big Strike\n* BMC\n* Brand-Rex\n* Cobridge Communications\n* Compudyne\n* Datablue\n* Diagnostic Health\n* DialGlobal\n* Elo Touch Solutions\n* equinox payments\n* etrali Trading Solutions\n* First Communications\n* Fotona\n* GTL\n* Glotel\n* Hay\n* inmac\n* J. Mendel\n* Lineage Power\n* [[Mexx]]\n* Millennium1 Solutions\n* National Envelope\n* Peoplenet\n* Powerwave Technologies\n* Proxicom\n* [[:nl:Real Software|Real Software]] ([[Belgium]])\n* Sage Automotive Interiors\n* Sagemcom\n* Scovill\n* Somero Enterprises, Inc.\n* The Clark Group, Inc.\n* Therakos, Inc.\n* Tweddle Group\n* Unify (formerly Siemens Enterprise Communication)\n* Unitedroad\n* Vincotech\n* Wire One Communications\n* Zmags\n{{Div col end}}\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official website|http://www.gores.com}}\n\n{{Private equity firms}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Gores Group}}\n[[Category:Private equity firms of the United States]]\n[[Category:Financial services companies established in 1987]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Los Angeles]]\n", "name_user": "MonsieurNeko", "label": "safe", "comment": "Corrected spelling of Enterasys", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Gores_Group"}
